{"lemma":"شَقِّ","slug":"شَقِّ","root":"ش.ق.ق","root_slug":"ش-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَقّ","root":"شقق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":17},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n22699","n22700"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make a cut or gap in; to cut into or through; to tear through; to transpierce; to cut into or through (something hard or rigid, for example, a skull, a roof, and so on, or a mass, for example, a rock), to bore through; to crack, to fissure","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make a cut or gap in; to cut into or through; to tear through; to transpierce; to cut into or through (something soft or pliable, for example, skin or a skin-covered body part such as a finger, a vein, flesh, or cloth or fabric, or a thickness or layer, for example, a paper, a sheet, or a leaf), to incise, to slit, to gash, to slash, to rip","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut through (something seemingly flat or level, such as a surface) parallelly;","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut through (something seemingly flat or level, such as a surface) parallelly;; to make a recess in; to groove; to furrow; to indent","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut in two or asunder, to tear apart, to split, to cleave","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut in two or asunder, to tear apart, to split, to cleave; to spread or cause disagreement or factionalism in or among; to divide, to rive","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to move or pass through; to cut across; to traverse, to cross","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لِلنَّجَاحِ، يَجِبُ عَلَى الْمَرْءِ أَنْ يَشُقَّ طَرِيقًا حَتَّى عِنْدَمَا تَظْهَرُ التَّحَدِّيَاتُ.","english":"To succeed, one must forge a path even when challenges arise."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to break or break forth, to come up, to erupt, to emerge","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become burdensome [with عَلَى (ʕalā) ‘for’], to be or become hard to bear for; to weigh down","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَقَّ (šaqqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","intransitive","noun-from-verb","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a gap; a gash; a fissure; a hollow, a cranny","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a recess; an indenture; a furrow","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"splitting, cleavage","tags":["intransitive","transitive","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fission","tags":["intransitive","transitive","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"half, side; part","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وأوضح أنه “ليس خافياً أنه كلف المدير العام للأمن العام اللواء عباس إبراهيم إدارة هذا الشق من الحوار الرسمي بين البلدين، بإزاء ما يرتبط بهذين الملفين”.","english":"He elucidated that “it isn’t a secret that he instructed the Director-General of Public Security, Major General Abbas Ibrahim, to manage this part of the official dialogue between the two countries, with respect to what is connected with these two files.”"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"double, doppelganger","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sex (male or female)","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʃaq.qa/","/ʃaqq/","/ʃiqq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22699","headword_ar":"شَقٌّ","root":"$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uquwqN","text_ar":"شُقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) originally an inf. n.; (S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An opening forming an interstice"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a thing: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fissure, cleft, chink, split, slit, rent, crack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadoEN","text_ar":"صَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in wood or a stick, or in a wall, or in a glass vessel [&c.]: (T, TA:) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place that is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oquwq","text_ar":"مَشْقُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloven"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleft, split,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (see 1, first sentence: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aq~N","text_ar":"مَشَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and often signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an incision, a gash,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a furrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trench"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) as though an inf. n. used as a subst. in this sense: pl. as above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uquwqN","text_ar":"شُقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) it differs from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uqaAqN","text_ar":"شُقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh,) by having a general signification: (Mgh:) accord. to Yaakoob, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyadi fulaAnK $uquwqN","text_ar":"بِيَدِ فُلَانٍ شُقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birijolihi","text_ar":"بِرِجْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm, of such a one are cracks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his foot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but [it is asserted that in this case] one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uqaAqN","text_ar":"شُقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh: [see, however, this word:]) and hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~u Alqabori","text_ar":"شَقُّ القَبْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The trench,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oblong excavation, in the middle of the grave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uquwqN","text_ar":"شُقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuduwE","text_ar":"صُدُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fissures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] in mountains, and in the earth, or ground. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rima vulvæ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman; i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gap"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chink"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two edges,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"borders, of the labia majora of her vulva:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aq~N","text_ar":"مَشَقٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daybreak."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)       -A2-  See also the next paragraph, first and fifth sentences.       -A3-  And see the last two sentences of the same paragraph."}],"source_refs":["Msb","T","TA","M","K","S","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n22700","headword_ar":"شِقٌّ","root":"$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) of a thing (S, Msb, K) of any kind; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~N","text_ar":"شَقٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing when it is cloven, or split, or divided lengthwise; (M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~apN","text_ar":"شِقَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn, S, * M, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu $iq~a Al$~aApi","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ شِقَّ الشَّاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~apa","text_ar":"شِقَّةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aApi","text_ar":"الشَّاةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took the half of the sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) the vulgar pronounce the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":"with fet-h. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o h`*aA Al$~iq~a","text_ar":"خُذْ هٰذَا الشِّقَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou this"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~ap","text_ar":"شِقَّة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSad~aquwA walawo bi$iq~i tamorapK","text_ar":"تَصَدَّقُوا وَلَوْ بِشِقِّ تَمْرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give ye alms though"},{"kind":"text","text":"it be but]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the half of a date;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning deem not anything little that is given as alms. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAlu bayoniY wabayonaka $iq~a Al$~aEarapi","text_ar":"المَالُ بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَكَ شِقَّ الشَّعَرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aEarapi","text_ar":"الشَّعَرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~a","text_ar":"شَقَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, * [in the CK and in my MS. copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$q~u","text_ar":"شقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former reading appears to be the right,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~a","text_ar":"شَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an inf. n. as in a similar saying in the former half of the first paragraph of this art., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~a","text_ar":"شِقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a subst. used as an inf. n. or for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka$iq~i","text_ar":"كَشِقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The property is between us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two halves, equal"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in division"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of the jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of diabolical beings having the form of the half of a human being."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw in his Descr. of the Jinn.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lateral half,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half and side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when one says that a person paralyzed has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"inclining; and as when one speaks of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHomil","text_ar":"مَحْمِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either of the two dorsers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panniers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oblong chests, which are borne, one on either side, by a camel, and which, with a small tent over them, compose a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHomil","text_ar":"مَحْمِل"},{"kind":"text","text":": see this last word, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArapN","text_ar":"مَحَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the body; as when one says of a person that his left"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was grazed, or abraded. (Mgh.) [Hence,] one says of a horse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiylu EalaY A^aHadi $iq~ayohi","text_ar":"يَمِيلُ عَلَى اَحَدِ شِقَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inclines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leans, upon one of his two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aY EalaY $iq~K","text_ar":"مَشَى عَلَى شِقٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY $iq~K","text_ar":"فِى شِقٍّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walked, inclining upon one side."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lateral part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Msb, K, TA,) of a thing; the two sides of a thing being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~aAhu","text_ar":"شِقَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, TA:) or, as some say, (TA,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side of a mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino $iq~i AlEa$iyrapi laA mino SamiymihaA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ شِقِّ العَشِيرَةِ لَا مِنْ صَمِيمِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the collateral class of the kinsfolk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribe, not of the main stock thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErD","text_ar":"عرض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqN","text_ar":"شَقِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) [which primarily signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloven-off half"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; i. e.,] when a thing is cloven in halves, each of the halves is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyq","text_ar":"شَقِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the other. (S, K.) ―         -b7-  [And hence, (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counterpart"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a person or thing: and this appears to be meant by J, and accord. to SM in the K, where it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~N","text_ar":"شِقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqN","text_ar":"شَقِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for they add immediately after:] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^axiY wa$iq~u","text_ar":"هُوَ اَخِى وَشِقُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosiY","text_ar":"نَفْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is my brother, and the counterpart of myself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) as though he were cloven from me, because of the resemblance of each of us to the other. (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h*aA","text_ar":"هذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyquhu","text_ar":"شَقِيقُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the like of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [hence] it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~isaA='u","text_ar":"النِّسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iqu Alr~ijaAli","text_ar":"شَقَايِقُ الرِّجَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"شَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqN","text_ar":"شَقِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as fem., or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqapN","text_ar":"شَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same sense,] meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women are the likes of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"in natural dispositions; as though they were cloven from them; or because Eve was created from Adam. (TA.) ―         -b8-  And (tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqN","text_ar":"شَقِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, O, K, TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a brother by the father and mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqN","text_ar":"شَقِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ either half of a thing that is cloven in halves; ” (S, TA;) or as though the relationship of one were cloven from that of the other: (IDrd, O, K:) pl. of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$iq~aA='u","text_ar":"اَشِقَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, Msb.) ―         -b9-  And a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing at which one looks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K:) [but this is app. taken from the following"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1578},{"kind":"text","text":"saying of Lth, in which I think"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iq~u","text_ar":"الشِّقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aq~u","text_ar":"الشَّقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ the crack, ” &c.:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aq~u","text_ar":"الشَّقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaqotu","text_ar":"شَقَقْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iq~u","text_ar":"الشِّقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name for that at which one looks [i. e. for the visible effect of the act signified by the verb], and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uquwqu","text_ar":"الشُّقُوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is well known as the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aq~u","text_ar":"الشَّقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JK.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aq~apN","text_ar":"مَشَقَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, Msb, K) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Difficulty, hardship, distress, affliction, trouble, inconvenience, fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weariness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lack of power, that overtakes the mind and the body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~N","text_ar":"شَقٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IJ, S, M, O, K;) thus it is sometimes pronounced with fet-h; mentioned by A'Obeyd; (S;) and by AZ; (M;) or this is an inf. n., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~N","text_ar":"شِقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the subst.; (O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uq~apN","text_ar":"شُقَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~apN","text_ar":"شِقَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signify the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aq~apN","text_ar":"مَشَقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as overtakes a man in consequence of travel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and the pls. of these two are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uqaqN","text_ar":"شُقَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) mentioned by Fr, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqaqN","text_ar":"شِقَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) mentioned on the authority of some one or more of [the tribe of] Keys: (TA:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aq~apN","text_ar":"مَشَقَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAq~u","text_ar":"مَشَاقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aq~aAtN","text_ar":"مَشَقَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence, in the Kur [xvi. 7],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo takuwnuwA baAligiyhi A_il~aA bi$iqi A@loA^anofusi","text_ar":"لَمْ تَكُونُوا بَالِغِيهِ اـِلَّا بِشِقِ ا@لْاَنْفُسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Which ye would not reach save with difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the souls"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; where some read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aq~i","text_ar":"بِشَقِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Lth","IDrd","O","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}